title: SmartWrite:紙のシンプルさを追求した手書きメモツールの開発 / SmartWrite: Peperlike pen-based memo tool pursued brevity
title_en: SmartWrite: Peperlike pen-based memo tool pursued brevity
abstract: 本研究は紙の手帖の迅速さと図入りメモの利便性を再現することを目的としたペン入力ベースの手書きメモ環境を開発した。 本研究はページ様式デザインや自動保存、JPEG/Exif形式によるファイル保存、写真のドラッグ＆ドロップ取り込み、モードレスなペンとキーボード入力などの機能を実装し、実使用で3週間に497枚、6か月に1,188枚のメモ作成記録を報告した。
abstract_en: This study developed a pen-based handwritten memo environment aimed at reproducing the speed and diagram-supporting convenience of paper notebooks. The study implemented page-style design, automatic saving, JPEG/Exif file storage, drag-and-drop photo import, and mode-less pen and keyboard input, and reported actual-use records of 497 memos in three weeks and 1,188 memos in six months.
positioning_summary: 本研究は既存の携帯端末やキーボード中心環境が起動や操作の手間、画面サイズや応答性、筆記の精細さによって速記や図入りメモに適さないというギャップを位置づけた。 本研究は日常的にアイデアを記録する利用者やヘビーユーザーを対象としてそのギャップを埋め、データ移動性や閲覧性、長期保存性の欠如に着目している。
positioning_summary_en: This study positions itself against the gap where existing mobile and keyboard-centered environments are unsuitable for quick handwritten and diagrammatic notes due to startup delay, screen size, responsiveness, and handwriting fidelity. The study targets everyday idea-recording users including heavy users and focuses on addressing issues of data mobility, viewability, and long-term preservation.
purpose_summary: 本研究の目的は紙の感覚を保ちながら電子メモの起動性や閲覧性、保存寿命を改善する手書きメモ環境を提供することであった。 本研究は手書きとキーボード入力の併用、写真とメモのシームレス統合、汎用画像形式による自動保存などを通じてデータ寿命と閲覧容易性を向上させることを目的とした。
purpose_summary_en: The purpose of this study was to provide a handwritten memo environment that preserves the feel of paper while improving electronic memo startup speed, viewability, and storage longevity. The study aimed to improve data lifetime and ease of viewing by supporting combined pen and keyboard input, seamless integration of photos and memos, and automatic saving in common image formats.
method_summary: 本研究はペン入力可能な表示一体型ノート型パソコン向けソフトとしてページ様式デザインや不要操作の排除などの設計原則に基づく機能群を実装した。 本研究はJPEG/Exifを用いたビットマップ保存、XML情報のJPEGコメントセグメントへの埋め込み、自動日付フォルダ化、背景画像と可動な写真オブジェクトのドラッグ＆ドロップ取り込み、モードレスな筆記とテキスト入力などの具体的実装を行った。
method_summary_en: The study implemented software for pen-enabled integrated-display notebook PCs based on design principles such as page-style layout and elimination of unnecessary operations. The implementation included bitmap saving using JPEG/Exif, embedding XML metadata into JPEG comment segments, automatic date-based foldering, drag-and-drop background and movable photo objects, and mode-less handwriting and text input.
evaluation_summary: 著者による実使用評価は主に観察的な使用記録の収集で行われ、実際の使用環境で数週間から数か月にわたる作成履歴を計測した。 著者による評価では本システムで3週間に497枚、6か月で1,188枚のメモ作成が記録され、評価期間中に紙メモ枚数が最終週に約4枚に減少するなど本システムへの移行を示唆する結果が観測された。
evaluation_summary_en: The evaluation conducted by the authors was primarily observational, collecting usage logs over several weeks to months in real-use environments. The authors' evaluation recorded 497 memos in three weeks and 1,188 memos in six months for the system, and observed a reduction of paper memos to about four in the final week, suggesting a shift toward the system.

Title: SmartWrite: Peperlike pen-based memo tool pursued brevity
Authors: Kaoru Misaki, Naoki Kato
Year: 2005
Abstract: This study developed a pen-based handwritten memo environment aimed at reproducing the speed and diagram-supporting convenience of paper notebooks. The study implemented page-style design, automatic saving, JPEG/Exif file storage, drag-and-drop photo import, and mode-less pen and keyboard input, and reported actual-use records of 497 memos in three weeks and 1,188 memos in six months.
Positioning Summary: This study positions itself against the gap where existing mobile and keyboard-centered environments are unsuitable for quick handwritten and diagrammatic notes due to startup delay, screen size, responsiveness, and handwriting fidelity. The study targets everyday idea-recording users including heavy users and focuses on addressing issues of data mobility, viewability, and long-term preservation.
Purpose Summary: The purpose of this study was to provide a handwritten memo environment that preserves the feel of paper while improving electronic memo startup speed, viewability, and storage longevity. The study aimed to improve data lifetime and ease of viewing by supporting combined pen and keyboard input, seamless integration of photos and memos, and automatic saving in common image formats.
Method Summary: The study implemented software for pen-enabled integrated-display notebook PCs based on design principles such as page-style layout and elimination of unnecessary operations. The implementation included bitmap saving using JPEG/Exif, embedding XML metadata into JPEG comment segments, automatic date-based foldering, drag-and-drop background and movable photo objects, and mode-less handwriting and text input.
Evaluation Summary: The evaluation conducted by the authors was primarily observational, collecting usage logs over several weeks to months in real-use environments. The authors' evaluation recorded 497 memos in three weeks and 1,188 memos in six months for the system, and observed a reduction of paper memos to about four in the final week, suggesting a shift toward the system.
